<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Have you already chosen </span><b>Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as </span><a href="http://www.asuaire.com/"><span style="font-weight: 400;">your next holiday destination</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">? You’ve made a good choice! It is not surprising that this country has become a favourite destination among young adventurers. There is so much to do in this wonderful country! You can get lost in the sounds of the jungle, see the amazing volcanoes or relax on the Caribbean coast. But there is one place that we are always recommending: the province of </span><b>Guanacaste in Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Do you have a few minutes? Have a read about everything </span><b>Guanacaste</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has to offer. We are sure that this dream destination will make you want to go and pack your bags and start exploring.</span></p>
<p><img class="size-full wp-image-20624" title="Manzanillo at Puerto Viejo Costa Rica" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Manzanillo at Puerto Viejo Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica.jpg" /><noscript><img class="size-full wp-image-20624" title="Manzanillo at Puerto Viejo Costa Rica" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica.jpg" alt="Manzanillo at Puerto Viejo Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Manzanillo-at-Puerto-Viejo-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<div id="toc_container" class="toc_light_blue no_bullets"><p class="toc_title">Contenido</p><ul class="toc_list"><li><ul><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li><li></li></ul></li><li><ul><li></li><li></li></ul></li></ul></div>
<h2><span id="Get_to_know_the_province_of_Guanacaste"><b>Get to know the province of Guanacaste</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Guanacaste </span><b>is the most northwesterly province in Costa Rica.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> One of its main characteristics is that, despite being the second largest region in Costa Rica, </span><b>it is the most sparsely populated.</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Only 326,953 people live in its extensive 10,140 km² area. Here you will find jungle, lush forests and natural parks, paradise beaches and some lost cities that are worth visiting—like </span><b>Liberia, Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, the capital of the Guanacaste province.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20630" title="LIBERIA COSTA RICA" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="LIBERIA COSTA RICA" width="1200" height="675" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20630" title="LIBERIA COSTA RICA" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg" alt="LIBERIA COSTA RICA" width="1200" height="675" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/LIBERIA-COSTA-RICA-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="What_is_there_to_see_and_do_in_Guanacaste"><span style="font-weight: 400;">What is there to see and do in Guanacaste?</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">First of all, write down the following list of recommendations on what to </span><b>see and do in Guanacaste</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> The city of </span><b>Liberia</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in Costa Rica.</span></li>
<li><b> The National Parks:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Barra Honda National Park, Diriá National Park, Guanacaste National Park, Las Baulas Marine National Park, Palo Verde National Park, Rincon de la Vieja National Park, Santa Rosa National Park, Tenorio Volcano National Park and Arenal Volcano National Park. </span></li>
<li><b> Guanacaste beaches</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: Visit the Coco, Tamarindo, Grande, Samara and Hermosa beaches.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23138" title="Imagenes blog-01-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23138" title="Imagenes blog-01-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-01-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<ul>
<li><b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Guanacaste </span><b>volcanoes </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">like the Rincon de la Vieja, Tenorio, Arenal, Miravalles and Orosí volcanoes.</span></li>
<li><b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Visit the </span><b>Puntarenas beaches</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, located in the province to the south and near Guanacaste.</span></li>
<li><b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> See the famous </span><b>leatherback turtles</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>
<li><b> Sports:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> There are many places that are great for hiking; there are also plenty of water sports like catamaran rides, surfing or boogieboarding and snorkelling.</span></li>
<li><b></b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Do not leave the country without trying Costa Rican </span><b>coffee</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and </span><b>chocolate</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Now do you have an idea of everything this region has to offer? So, why not pack your bags and</span><b> set off on an adventure to Guanacaste</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">?</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23136" title="Imagenes blog-02-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23136" title="Imagenes blog-02-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-02-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h2><span id="Liberia_Costa_Rica_the_capital_of_Guanacaste"><b>Liberia, Costa Rica, the capital of Guanacaste</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you like, you can </span><b>stay in Liberia</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or just visit it, because this city is well connected for reaching other attractions in Guanacaste. It has its own international airport. From Liberia you can take the so-called </span><b>highway 21</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or </span><b>Calle Real</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which takes you to other cities like Nicoya and Carmona. The road also has various roads leading off it that will take you to other villages and places of interest for tourists.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The colonial city of Liberia is a popular tourist destination with some points of interest of its own. It has </span><b>beautiful churches</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, a </span><b>central park</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and the </span><a href="http://museodeguanacaste.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Guanacaste Museum</b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which we recommend you visit if you want to learn a little more about the history of this fantastic destination.</span></p>
<p><img class="size-full wp-image-20628" title="Corcovado National Park in Costa Rica" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Corcovado National Park in Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica.jpg" /><noscript><img class="size-full wp-image-20628" title="Corcovado National Park in Costa Rica" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica.jpg" alt="Corcovado National Park in Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Corcovado-National-Park-in-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The city has just over 55,000 inhabitants and you can also enjoy the lively nightlife in its restaurants and bars. From Liberia you can visit the great white sand beaches, the province’s jungles and volcanoes. Also, there are plenty of places to stay in Liberia or Guanacaste.</span></p>
<p><a href="https://asuaire.com/en/costarica/hotels/hilton-garden-inn-liberia-airport"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hilton Garden Inn Liberia Airport</span></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Hilton Garden Inn Liberia Airport is a great place to start and finish your holiday. Located in the province of Guanacaste, right next to Liberia airport, it has all the facilities you need to enjoy the start of your trip through beautiful Guanacaste. </span></p>
<h3><span id="Hotel_Bosque_del_Mar"><a href="https://asuaire.com/costarica/hoteles/bosque-del-mar"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hotel Bosque del Mar</span></a></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hotel Bosque del Mar, located </span><b>by Hermosa Beach in Guanacaste </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">is another great place to stay, and comes recommended by our agency. Here you can relax during a wonderful stay surrounded by greenery.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://asuaire.com/costarica/hoteles/bosque-del-mar"><b>Bosque del Mar hotel</b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> has great facilities like a swimming pool, jacuzzi and an international restaurant. It also provides information and reservations for excursions. You are sure to love it!</span></p>
<h2><span id="Guanacaste_parks_and_nature_reserves"><b>Guanacaste parks and nature reserves</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The province is full of them and, depending on the length of your stay, you might be able to see all of them. We will recommend the best ones to visit. We know you will love Costa Rica’s flora and fauna.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20626" title="Tortuguero National Park Costa Rica" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%201200%20675'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="Tortuguero National Park Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-20626" title="Tortuguero National Park Costa Rica" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica.jpg" alt="Tortuguero National Park Costa Rica" width="1200" height="675" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica.jpg 1200w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Tortuguero-National-Park-Costa-Rica-600x338.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Palo_Verde_National_Park"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Palo Verde National Park</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This region is in the very south of Guanacaste province, but it is worth going to see the wildlife that live in the forests here.</span><b> Palo Verde</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is an area of </span><b>wetlands, grasslands and tropical forests</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It stands out for its aquatic species and for the diversity of </span><b>migratory birds</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> that stop in the park. But the surprises don&#8217;t end there! The park is also home to a large number of reptiles like iguanas and whiptail lizards. </span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23134" title="Imagenes blog-03-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23134" title="Imagenes blog-03-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-03-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Be sure to go with a guide, as there are rattlesnakes and coral snakes and even </span><b>huge American crocodiles!</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Other animals you&#8217;ll find are sloths, coyotes and deer; there are also howler and white-faced monkeys. Some of the most interesting species are the peccaries &#8211; similar to wild boars &#8211; and the unusual agouties. The </span><b>puma</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> also lives in this natural environment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Palo Verde is only for the adventurous traveller. Dare you set foot here so you can say you&#8217;ve been?</span></p>
<h3><span id="Monteverde_Cloud_Forest_Biological_Reserve"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Monteverde Cloud Forest Biological Reserve</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Every ecotourism lover must visit the </span><b>Monteverde Cloud Forest</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, in </span><b>Costa Rica’s Tilarán mountain range</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Dare to step onto one of the suspension bridges to see the Cloud Forest’s diverse flora in more detail. Do you know where the name comes from? It’s because it lies thousands of feet above sea level, which means that this forest is so high you can walk through the clouds.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23132" title="Imagenes blog-04-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23132" title="Imagenes blog-04-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-04-min-3-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The Cloud Forest is not just in Guanacaste, much of the area lies in the neighbouring province of Puntarenas. With a bit of luck, you will see </span><b>toucans, hummingbirds</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and other rare birds like trogons and bellbirds. This </span><b>biological reserve has 26,000 acres</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of land for you to lose yourself in.</span></p>
<h2><span id="Guanacaste_beaches"><b>Guanacaste beaches</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These are one of the reasons we decided to take an adventure to the American continent. The experience of relaxing on the pristine and natural beaches is priceless. Costa Rica has many of them and there are enough in Guanacaste alone that you won’t need to visit all of them. Here are some.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23130" title="Imagenes blog-05-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23130" title="Imagenes blog-05-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-05-min-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Playas_del_Coco"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Playas del Coco</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">They are sunny and fun. This set of beaches stands out for the various activities that you can enjoy there. You will find a youthful and casual atmosphere, alongside </span><b>fishing, water sports</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and plenty of fun.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23128" title="Imagenes blog-06-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23128" title="Imagenes blog-06-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-06-min-1-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Tamarindo_beach"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tamarindo beach</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">There is so much to say about this beautiful place. It is actually </span><b>a bay </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">formed by the meeting point of Grande beach and Ventanas beach. The Tamarindo Grande beach is located to the north and is perfect for relaxing, as there are not too many people. This beach it known for its good waves, so </span><b>surfing</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is very common here.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23126" title="Imagenes blog-07-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23126" title="Imagenes blog-07-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-07-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The </span><a href="https://www.govisitcostarica.co.cr/region/city.asp?cID=24" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Tamarindo</b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> area is home to the Matapalo river and native vegetation like coconut palms, tamarinds and savanna oaks. Nearby there are plenty of restaurants and a good nightlife. Thanks to its cleanliness and safety, this beach has won the </span><a href="https://asuaire.com/blog/costa-rica/certificado-bandera-azul"><b>Ecological Blue Flag Award</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></a></p>
<h3><span id="Samara_beach"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Samara beach</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This is another bay stretching about 4 km with clear sand and gentle waves. This beach is located in the south of the province, next to a small town. It is a quiet and very safe place. From </span><b>Samara beach</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> you can see the</span><b> Chora island</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and the </span><b>coral reefs</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. You will love diving through the clear waters. No doubt about it! Take the opportunity as well to visit the </span><b>lovely town of Samara</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. This beach also has a </span><b>Blue Flag</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23124" title="Imagenes blog-08-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23124" title="Imagenes blog-08-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-08-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Hermosa_beach"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Hermosa beach</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The main feature of </span><b>Hermosa beach</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is the </span><b>grey sand</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Its waters are perfect for </span><b>snorkelling and diving</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">; also for leisurely fishing and sailing. Out of the water, you can tour the coast on horseback.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23122" title="Imagenes blog-09-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23122" title="Imagenes blog-09-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-09-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Nosara_beach_and_Guiones_beach"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Nosara beach and Guiones beach</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">These are long coasts with white sand and strong waves. One of the experiences that the beach provides is in the area called </span><b>Punta Nosara</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, where you can see </span><b>the rocks breaking the waves</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. The 3 km of Nosara beach has enough space for long walks. The Nosara river flows here, which forms a very beautiful mangrove next to the beach. As you might imagine, this is a great place to surf. Because of the tranquility and peace, </span><b>Nosara beach and Guiones beach</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> have become a place of </span><b>spiritual retreat and yoga</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> for travellers looking to unwind.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23120" title="Imagenes blog-10-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23120" title="Imagenes blog-10-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-10-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h2><span id="Visit_Guanacastes_volcanoes"><b>Visit Guanacaste’s volcanoes</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Costa Rica is a region of </span><b>significant volcanic activity</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. We recommend visiting some volcanoes during your visit to Guanacaste province. They are as imposing as they are beautiful.</span></p>
<h3><span id="Rincon_de_la_Vieja"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rincon de la Vieja</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This volcano is in the </span><a href="http://www.sinac.go.cr/ES/ac/acg/pnrv/Paginas/default.aspx" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><b>Rincon de la Vieja</b></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> national park. You can travel from </span><b>Liberia</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, as it is only 15 miles northeast of the city. The </span><b>volcano</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is one of the area’s attractions, but not the only one. You will also see waterfalls and </span><b>natural pools</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. </span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23118" title="Imagenes blog-11-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23118" title="Imagenes blog-11-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-11-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Be careful because the volcano is active! Access to the crater is permanently prohibited and if there is an eruption, the Rincon de la Vieja National Park is completely closed. Be sure to check with </span><a href="https://asuaire.com/costarica/tours/aventuras-volcanicas-singulares-rincon-la-vieja"><span style="font-weight: 400;">your Asuaire Travel advisor </span></a></p>
<h3><span id="Tenorio_volcano"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tenorio volcano</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The national park where this volcano is located is in the neighbouring province of Alajuela. In fact, if you decide to visit it, we suggest you also go and see the striking </span><b>blue green waterfall of the Celeste River</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in the national park. </span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23116" title="Imagenes blog-12-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23116" title="Imagenes blog-12-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-12-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You might spend more time there than at the volcano itself (which is also amazing). It is a huge </span><b>inactive double crater volcano</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Take in everything this environment has to offer you and take photos to look back on. There is no other landscape like it in the world. </span></p>
<h3><span id="Arenal_volcano"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Arenal volcano</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is located in the </span><b>Arenal Volcano National Park</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. It is still active and has a sad history. An eruption in 1968 swept away several nearby villages. As with the Tenorio volcano, the national park itself is in Alajuela and not in Guanacaste, although it’s close to the border. Here you should visit the </span><b>lava trails</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> and, perhaps, one of the many hot spring spas.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21916" title="Imagenes blog-03" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-600x337.jpg 600w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-21916" title="Imagenes blog-03" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/Imagenes-blog-03-1-600x337.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<h3><span id="Miravalles_volcano"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Miravalles volcano</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This volcano lies at an altitude of 2,028 metres above sea level, in the </span><b>Guanacaste volcanic mountain range</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. What is the strangest thing about the area? You will be surprised by the </span><b>yellow hot springs</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> (because of the volcanic minerals).</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23112" title="Imagenes blog-14-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23112" title="Imagenes blog-14-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-14-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><b>Miravalles</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> is one of five active volcanoes in Costa Rica. In the </span><b>Hornillas </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">area, you can walk on one of its craters. From there you will be able to see the hot mud, the fumaroles and the sulphur rivers. </span><b>It is said that volcanic minerals have healing properties</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">.</span></p>
<h3><span id="Orosi_volcano"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Orosí volcano</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This stratovolcano is also located in the mountain range, within the Guanacaste national park. It is part of the </span><b>Guanacaste Conservation Area</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, which has been declared a World Heritage Site by Unesco. </span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23110" title="Imagenes blog-15-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23110" title="Imagenes blog-15-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-15-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is believed that the </span><b>last eruption of Orosí took</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> place in 3500 B. C. It is actually part of a group of adjoining volcanoes, which make up the Orosí-Cacao Volcano Complex; it includes the Orosí, Cacao, Orosilito, Pedregal and a fifth nameless volcano. If you visit the national park, take the opportunity to have a look at this </span><b>impressive complex.</b></p>
<h2><span id="Interesting_facts_about_Costa_Rica_for_visitors"><b>Interesting facts about Costa Rica for visitors.</b></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">If you are almost ready to book your trip, let us give you some final tips to make the most of your stay. It is better to take your </span><b>trip to Guanacaste</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> with some questions answered.</span></p>
<h3><span id="What_is_the_weather_like_in_Costa_Rica"><span style="font-weight: 400;">What is the weather like in Costa Rica?</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Actually, Costa Rica’s climate depends on where you go as it has dozens of microclimates. Should you put swimwear in your suitcase? </span><b>Yes</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">, definitely. But you won’t want to swim at all the beaches. As we have said, the natural park areas are rainy.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23108" title="Imagenes blog-16-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23108" title="Imagenes blog-16-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-16-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;"> On other beaches, the waves are so strong that swimming is prohibited. To enjoy the sun and go swimming, visit Tamarindo, Flamingo or Sámara, as well as some others. Ask your Asuaire Travel advisor who will recommend the best beach for the activities you want to enjoy. </span></p>
<h3><span id="Is_Costa_Rica_safe"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Is Costa Rica safe?</span></span></h3>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In general, since Costa Rica is very poplar with tourists, </span><b>Costa Ricans tend to treat travellers well</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. However, you should always follow the advice of experts. You should write down the </span><b>telephone number of your country’s embassy</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> in Costa Rica.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">It is important to remember that if you are a woman and travelling alone you must be extra careful and not go into dark, unknown or secluded places. This advice of course also applies to men. You also need to look out for </span><b>seismic and volcanic activity</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> as well as road safety.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23106" title="Imagenes blog-17-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23106" title="Imagenes blog-17-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog-17-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">You should not use unofficial taxis or have your valuables visible. In urban areas, be especially vigilant with your luggage and belongings. </span><b>Always avoid dangerous parts</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> of cities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The diseases you are most at risk from are </span><b>dengue, chikungunya, zika and malaria</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Always wear long clothes (shirt and trousers) to avoid mosquito bites; and remember to immediately cover your bottles of water and juice after drinking. Do not drink water from rural areas, use your own bottled water instead. We recommend travelling with medical insurance.</span></p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23140" title="Imagenes blog_Mesa de trabajo 58-min" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20viewBox='0%200%202500%201406'%3E%3C/svg%3E" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" data-lazy-srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" data-lazy-sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" data-lazy-src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min.jpg" /><noscript><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-23140" title="Imagenes blog_Mesa de trabajo 58-min" src="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" srcset="https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min.jpg 2500w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-510x287.jpg 510w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-900x506.jpg 900w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-768x432.jpg 768w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://asuaire.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/Imagenes-blog_Mesa-de-trabajo-58-min-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /></noscript></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Staying in tourist areas and taking some precautions, your stay in </span><b>Guanacaste Costa Rica</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> should be </span><b>safe and enjoyable</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">. What are you waiting for? Go and enjoy one of their slushies or typical cocktails under a coconut tree!</span></p>
		</div>

